#   HEAD-004: `be head be://` fetches subs from `.gitmodules` URL, not parent

For a `be://` (beagle-scheme) remote, `be head` recursing into a submodule
goes STRAIGHT to the sub's declared `.gitmodules` URL instead of fetching the
sub from the SAME parent source first. `be head be://localhost/beagle` reached
into `abc` and tried `https://github.com/gritzko/libabc.git` over ssh â†’
`github.com:22` refused â†’ `WIREUNRCH`, aborting the whole peek. A beagle parent
keeps every sub in its own shard ([Submodules]/[submodule-parent-source-fetch]),
so the parent source MUST be the primary candidate; the declared URL is a
fallback used only when the parent has no copy. `be get` already forwards
`--source` (GET-011); HEAD's recursion does not. Relates to [HEAD-003].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Repro (from `~/todo/DIS-045`): `be head be://localhost/beagle` â†’
    `be: head .`, `be: head abc`, then `ssh: connect to host github.com port 22:
    Connection refused`, `remote https://github.com/gritzko/libabc.git is
    unreachable`, `Error: WIREUNRCH`, `BEDOGEXIT` â€” the peek dies on a sub fetch.
 -  The sub `abc`/`libabc` lives in the parent shard; `be://localhost/beagle`
    can serve it. Going to github first is both wrong and fatal when offline.
 -  `be get` forwards the in-flight source as `--source <src_uri>` so sniff's
    SubMount builds the PRIMARY candidate from the same remote
    (`beagle/SUBS.c:485-502`, GET-011). HEAD's sub recursion omits it.

### Goals
 -  `be head be://<parent>` resolves each sub's pin from the PARENT source
    first; the `.gitmodules` URL is tried only if the parent lacks the objects.
 -  A dead declared URL (github offline) does NOT fail the peek when the parent
    can serve the sub â€” no `WIREUNRCH` abort.

### Constraints
 -  be-scheme parents only; a git-source parent keeps git's own recursion
    (the `--source` flag is omitted when empty â€” `SUBS.c:488`).
 -  Fallback order is parent-source â†’ declared `.gitmodules` URL, in that order;
    never the reverse ([submodule-parent-source-fetch]).

